# Web Client (React)

## Invariant

All API calls go through the Vite proxy (`/api/*`) — do not hardcode server URLs in components.

## Stack

- React + Vite + pnpm
- Port **5174** for monolith (5173 is microservices)
- Proxy to `cortex-server:8000`

## API paths

- Auth: JWT Bearer from `/auth/login`
- Documents: `/cases/{id}/documents`, `/documents/{id}`
- Chat: `/chat/*`
- Sync: `/cases/{id}/sync`, `/sync/{jobId}`
- AI: `/rag`, `/laws`, `/translate`

## When backend routes change

1. Identify the owning module (not always platform)
2. Update frontend fetch paths if API broke
3. Test login → cases → sync → search → chat

## Style

- Functional components; hooks for reusable logic
- No extra state library unless needed
- TypeScript strict; types aligned with backend schemas

